text: The 1993–94 Algerian Championnat National was the 32nd season of the Algerian Championnat National since its establishment in 1962. A total of 16 teams contested the league, with MC Oran as the defending champions, The Championnat started on November 18, 1993. and ended on June 16, 1994. ==Team summaries== === Promotion and relegation === Teams promoted from Algerian Division 2 1993–1994 * CS Constantine * GC Mascara * ASO Chlef Teams relegated to Algerian Division 2 1994–1995 * WA Mostaganem * ES Sétif * USM Bel-Abbès ==League table== ==References== ==External links== *1993–94 Algerian Championnat National Algerian Championnat National Championnat National Category:Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1 seasons
